{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"All direct and transitive dependencies are extracted from the manifest and included in the vulnerability check.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure typically appears at the boundary between manifest parsing, dependency graph resolution (including transitives), and request assembly. A unit test of only the parser or only the resolver can miss handoff bugs where transitives are dropped.","test_description":"Run scanner components together on a fixture project (e.g., package.json + lockfile / requirements + lock data) and assert the final vulnerability-check payload contains both direct and transitive dependencies with expected versions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The vulnerability database query returns results that match the exact version ranges in the manifest, not just the package name.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior depends on real API query semantics for version-range matching. Mocks can return idealized data and hide real mismatches in request format, encoding, or server-side interpretation.","test_description":"Against a real vuln DB endpoint (or vendor-provided live sandbox), submit dependencies with controlled version ranges and assert returned CVEs correspond only to affected ranges, not all versions of the package.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The severity sorting places Critical above High above Medium above Low, with CVEs of the same severity sorted by CVSS score.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Pure deterministic ordering logic over local data; no module interaction or external dependency is required to expose the failure.","test_description":"Feed an unsorted in-memory CVE list with mixed severities and CVSS values into the sorter and assert exact output order (severity precedence, then descending CVSS within severity).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.93,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The manifest modification changes only the affected dependency's version, leaving all other entries unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real risk is in parser/editor/serializer interaction (and potentially multi-format support), where unrelated entries can be reordered or mutated during write-back.","test_description":"Apply the update pipeline to fixture manifests containing multiple dependencies and formatting quirks, then compare before/after to verify only the target dependency version changed and all other entries are byte- or semantically-identical per format rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Requires real git/hosting API behavior (branching, commit, PR creation, rendered diff). Mocking can hide auth, branch protection, diff composition, and API contract failures.","test_description":"Run scanner against a real test repository and verify a PR is opened, then assert changed files/diff contain exactly one dependency-version update and no unrelated modifications.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Semver major-bump detection is deterministic local logic and can be validated fully without I/O or cross-module wiring.","test_description":"Test semver comparison function with representative cases (1.2.3->2.0.0, 1.2.3->1.3.0, pre-release/build metadata) and assert only major increments are flagged as breaking.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.95,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is in orchestration: semver decision must propagate to PR-creation gate and reporting output consistently. A unit test of only the decision function cannot catch miswiring.","test_description":"Execute scanner flow with a fixture vulnerability requiring a major bump; assert output includes review-required flag and PR module is not invoked (or no PR artifact is produced) while other scan reporting still completes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}}]}
